: Hooked bear, In the bag: [Bill Thompson]. The story of Anyburg, U.S.A.: [Hans Conried, Thurl Ravenscroft, Bill Thompson]. Paul Bunyon: [Thurl Ravenscroft]. Noah's ark: narrator, Jerome Courtland ; Jeanne Gayle, James MacDonald, Paul Frees. Goliath II: narrated by Sterling Holloway ; [Barbara Jo Allen, Kevin Corcoran, Verna Felton, Paul Frees, J. Pat O'Malley. The saga of Windwagon Smith: Rex Allen and the Sons of the Pioneers. A symposium on popular songs: Paul Frees, Gloria Wood, Billy Storm, Skip Farrell.  aDisc 1: Alice's wonderland: photography by Ubbe Iwwerks and Rudolph Ising ; technical direction by Hugh Harman and Carman Maxwell ; music composed by Alexander Rannie. Alice's wild West show, Alice gets in dutch, Alice's egg plant, Alice in the jungle, Alice's mysterious mystery, Alice the whaler: music composed by Alexander Rannie. Ferdinand the bull: adapted from the story and illustrations by Munro Leaf & Robert Lawson. The brave engineer: animation, Milt Kahl, Fred Moore, Al Bertino ; story, Dick Kinney, Dick Shaw ; musical score, Ken Darby. Morris the midget moose: animation, George Nicholas [and others] ; story, Eric Gurney, Bill de la Torre ; music, Oliver Wallace. Lambert the sheepish lion: story, Bill Peet, Ralph Wright, Milt Banta ; music, Joseph S. Dubin ; animation, Eric Larson [and others]. The little house: animation, Marc Davis, Les Clark, Clair Weeks ; music, Paul Smith ; story adaptation, Bill Peet, Bill Cottrell. Adventures in music: story, Dick Huemer ; music, Joseph D. Dubin ; art director, Kendal O'Connor ; animators, Ward Kimball [and others] ; songs, Sonny Burke, Paul Webster. Football now and then: animation, John Sibley, George Nicholas, Fred Moore ; story, Lance Nolley ; music, Edward Plumb. Toot, whistle, plunk and boom: story, Dick Huemer ; music, Joseph Dubin ; art direction, A-Kendall O'Connor ; animators, Ward Kimball [and others]. Ben and me: story, Bill Peet ; story adaptation, Winston Hibler, Del Connell, Ted Sears ; animation, Wolfgang Reitherman [and others] ; art direction, Ken Anderson, Claude Coats ; music by Oliver Wallace.  aDisc 2: Pigs is pigs: animation, John Sibley ; story, Leo Salkin ; music, Oliver Wallce. Social lion: animation, Norman Ferguson ; story, Milt Schaffer, Dick Kinney ; music, Oliver Wallace. Hooked bear: animation, Bill Justice [and others] ; story, Al Bertino, Dave Detiege ; music, Oliver Wallace. Jack and old Mac: animation, Al Cole, Bob Carlson, Jack Parr ; story, Dick Kinney, Roy Williams ; music, George Bruns. In the bag: animation, John Sibley [and others] ; story, Dave Detiege, Al Bertino ; music, George Bruns. A cowboy needs a horse: animation, Cliff Nordberg [and others] ; story, Dick Kinney, Roy Williams ; music, George Bruns ; song by Paul Mason Howard, Billy Mills. The story of Anyburg, U.S.A.: story, Dick Huemer ; music, Joseph S. Dubin ; animation, John Sibley, Bob Carlson, George Kreisl. The truth about Mother Goose: story, Bill Peet ; animation, Cliff Nordberg [and others] ; music, George Bruns ; lyrics, Tom Adair, Bill Peet, George Bruns ; vocals, The Page Cavanaugh Trio. Paul Bunyan: story by Lance Nolley, Ted Berman ; animation, John Sibley ; music, George Bruns ; lyrics, Tom Adair ; vocals, The Mellomen. Noah's Ark: music, George Bruns ; songs, Mel Leven ; story by T. Hee. Goliath II: story by Bill Peet ; directing animator, John Lounsbery ; music, George Bruns. The saga of Windwagon Smith: story, Lance Nolley, C. August Nichols ; production design, Erni Nordli ; animation, Julius Svendsen, Art Stevens ; music, George Bruns ; lyrics, C. August Nichols. A symposium on popular songs: story and styling, Xavier Atencio ; stop motion, Bill Justice ; animation, Eric Larson [and others] ; words and music by Richard M. Sherman and Robert B. Sherman ; arranged and conducted by Camarata.  aOriginally produced as 32 short animated films between 1923-1962.  aCollective title from disc menu & container; individual titles from screen.  aBooklet includes an essay by film historian Leonard Maltin.  aMelody and Toot, whistle, plunk and boom originally produced as episodes of the Adventures in Music series.  aA collection of rare animated films by Walt Disney Productions.0 aDisc 1 (162 min.): Alice's Wonderland (1923) ; Alice's wild West show (1924) ; Alice gets in dutch (1924) ; Alice's egg plant (1925) ; Alice in the jungle (1925) ; Alice's mysterious mystery (1926) ; Alice the whaler (1927) ; Ferdinand the bull (1938) ; Chicken Little (1943) ; The pelican and the snipe (1944) ; The brave engineer (1950) ; Morris the midget moose (1950) ; Lambert the sheepish lion (1952) ; The little house (1952) ; Melody (1953) ; Football now and then (1953) ; Toot, whistle, plunk and boom (1953) ; Ben and me (1953) -- Disc 2 (164 min.): Pigs is pigs (1954) ; Social lion (1954) ; Hooked bear (1956) ; Jack and old Mac (1956) ; In the bag (1956) ; A cowboy needs a horse (1956) ; The story of Anyburg, U.S.A. (1957) ; The truth about Mother Goose (1957) ; Paul Bunyan (1958) ; Noah's Ark (1959) ; Goliath II (1960) ; The saga of Windwagon Smith (1961) ; A symposium on popular songs (1962, with optional audio commentary by film historian Leonard Maltin & composer Richard Sherman) ; Bonus cartoon: A feather in his collar (1946).0 aDisc 1 (162 min.): Alice's wonderland (1923, 13 min.) / Laugh-O-Gram Films Inc. present ; scenario and direction by Walt Disney ; an Alice comedy -- Alice's wild West show (1924, 13 min.) / M.J. Winkler presents ; a Walt Disney comic -- Alice gets in dutch (1924, 10 min.) / M.J. Winkler presents ; by Walt Disney ; an Alice comedy ; a Walt Disney comic -- Alice's egg plant (1925, 9 min.) / M.J. Winkler presents ; by Walt Disney ; an Alice comedy -- Alice in the jungle (1925, 8 min.) / M.J. Winkler presents ; by Walt Disney ; an Alice comedy -- Alice's mysterious mystery (1926, 6 min.) / M.J. Winkler presents ; by Walt Disney ; an Alice comedy -- Alice the whaler (1927, 6 min.) / Joseph P. Kennedy presents ; a Winkler picture by Walt Disney ; an Alice comedy ; an F.B.O. picture -- Ferdinand the bull (1938, 8 min.) / Walt Disney presents -- Chicken Little (1943, 9 min.) / a Walt Disney production -- The pelican and the snipe (1944, 9 min.) / a Walt Disney production -- The brave engineer (1950, 8 min.) / Walt Disney presents ; based on the Ballad of Casey Jones by T. Lawrence Seibert and Eddie Newton ; direction, Jack Kinney -- Morris the midget moose (1950, 8 min.) / a Walt Disney production ; direction, Charles Nichols ; original story by Frank Owen -- Lambert the sheepish lion (1952, 8 min.) / Walt Disney presents ; direction, Jack Hannah -- The little house (1952, 8 min.) / Walt Disney presents ; direction, Wilfred Jackson ; from the book by Virginia Lee Burton -- Melody (1953, 10 min.) / RKO Radio Pictures ; Walt Disney presents ; directors, C. August Nichols, Ward Kimball -- Football now and then (1953, 8 min.) / a Walt Disney production ; direction, Jack Kinney -- Toot, whistle, plunk and boom (1953, 10 min.) / Walt Disney presents ; directors, C. August Nichols, Ward Kimball -- Ben and me (1953, 21 min.) / a Walt Disney production ; original story, Robert Lawson ; direction, Hamilton Luske.0 aDisc 2 (164 min.): Pigs is pigs (1954, 10 min.) / a Walt Disney production ; direction, Jack Kinney ; from the book by Ellis Parker Butler -- Social lion (1954, 7 min.) / a Walt Disney production ; direction, Jack Kinney -- Hooked bear (1956, 6 min.) / RKO Pictures ; a Walt Disney cartoon ; direction, Jack Hannah -- Jack and old Mac (1956, 7 min.) / Walt Disney presents ; direction, Bill Justice -- In the bag (1956, 8 min.) / RKO Pictures ; a Walt Disney cartoon ; direction, Jack Hannah -- A cowboy needs a horse (1956, 7 min.) / Walt Disney presents ; director, Bill Justice -- The story of Anyburg, U.S.A. (1957, 11 min.) / a Walt Disney production ; directed by Clyde Geronimi -- The truth about Mother Goose (1957, 15 min.) / a Walt Disney cartoon ; direction, Wolfgang Reitherman, Bill Justice -- Paul Bunyan (1958, 17 min.) / Walt Disney presents ; directed by Les Clark -- Noah's Ark (1959, 21 min.) / Walt Disney presents ; directed by Bill Justice -- Goliath II (1960, 15 min.) / Walt Disney presents ; directed by Wolfgang Reitherman -- The saga of Windwagon Smith (1961, 13 min.) / Walt Disney presents ; directed by C. August Nichols -- A symposium on popular songs (1962, 20 min.) / Walt Disney presents ; directed by Bill Justice -- Bonus cartoon: A feather in his collar (1946, 2 min.) / Walt Disney Productions.  aBonus features: Disc 1: Introduction by film historian Leonard Maltin (4 min.); Alice's cartoon world : an interview with Virginia Davis (12 min., interviewed by Leonard Maltin); From Kansas City to Hollywood : a timeline of Disney's silent era featurette (8 min.).  aBonus features: Disc 2: Introduction by film historian Leonard Maltin (3 min.); A symposium on popular songs audio commentary by Richard Sherman; "A feather in his collar" (bonus short); Galleries (7 animation art galleries): Ferdinand the bull, The little house, The story of Anyburg, USA, Chicken Little, Paul Bunyan, The truth about Mother Goose, A cowboy needs a horse.  aFerdinand the Bull: Academy Award for Best Short Subject, Cartoons.  aToot, whistle, plunk and boom: Academy Award for Best Short Subject, Cartoons. 0aBullsvDrama.0n001001 7aBulls.2fast0n001001 7aFeature films.2fast0n001001 7aVideo recordings for the hearing impaired.2fast0n001001 7aJuvenile works.2fast0n001001 7aAnimated films.2fast0n001001 7aChildren's films.2fast0n001001 7aDrama.2fast0n001001 7aFilms for the hearing impaired.2fast0n001001 7aShort films.2fast0n001001 7aAnimated films.2gsafd0n001001 7aShort films.2gsafd0n001001 7aAnimated films.2lcgft0n001001 7aShort films.2lcgft0n001001 7aChildren's films.2lcgft0n001001 7aFilms for the hearing impaired.2lcgft0n001001 7aVideo recordings for the hearing impair